      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KING CHERRY (6) has been hard to follow lately, running seventh (19.91) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. This looks easier and expected to bounce back. MR. FAHRENHEIT (3) turned in a plain effort last time when seventh at Warragul over 400m behind Rhine Star (23.82) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Comes through a solid form race last start. Likely to be thereabouts. SODA TURKEY (5) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by a nose at this track in a handy 17.08 beating Take A Phoenix. Looks a key chance if runs up to latest figure. JAY'S GIRL (1) is one of the chances after a minor prize at this track and distance last time.",
